### Summary

| Current Rec | Total | No Conflict | Conflict | Conflict % |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| Optimize | 27 | 4 | 23 | 85% |
| Consolidate | 22 | 8 | 14† | 64% |
| Terminate | 337 | 295 | 42 | 12% |
| **TOTAL** | **386** | **307** | **79** | **20%** |

**Key interpretation:**

The 23 Optimize→Consolidate conflicts are the most strategically significant finding. They reveal that "Optimize" was applied operationally as shorthand for *right-size and renegotiate* — which is correct tactically, but these 23 vendors (Score 2–3) do not have the mission-critical profile that the Optimize label implies. The four confirmed Score 4–5 Optimize vendors (Salesforce, AWS, Google, Microsoft) are the genuine strategic core.

The 42 Terminate→Consolidate conflicts represent recurring vendor relationships — recurring SaaS subscriptions, staffing PSLs, regional telecom and facilities — that were treated as one-off spend but carry consolidation value. Sage ($46K), Workato ($16K), Peakon ($17K), and Cognism ($27K) are the highest-priority corrections before Step 09 strategy is finalized.